--- SMD_TS1_TS2 ---

Steered MD stage generating the starting configurations for the TS1 <-> TS2 umbrella-sampling
scan (see ../USW_100_TS1_TS2/README and ../README). Unlike the reactant->TS PMF pipelines
(which pull 'dD'), this connection is driven along 'cobh' (COORDINATION of the leaving-group
oxygens with the surrounding hydrogens — tracks the coordination-sphere reorganization of the
leaving phosphate group between the two stationary points): MOVINGRESTRAINT pulls cobh from
AT0=1.7 to AT1=2.9 over 100000 steps, KAPPA=200 kcal/mol/A^2, under the same background wall
restraints as the reactant-side pipelines (see PMF_react_TS1/SMD_react_TS1/README for the
shared CV/wall definitions). Restart snapshots are converted the same way into 'lmp_files/'
seed structures for the umbrella windows.

Each replica also has a 'first_try/' subfolder — a complete earlier attempt at this same SMD
pull (same file set: trajectory, restarts, COLVAR, logs), superseded by the run in the
replica's top level but kept for reference.

Three replicas (rep1/2/3) — one README covers all three.

Note: this README documents pre-existing content; no existing file was modified.
